\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 489.157, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Task T-020@20260416T054258Z completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-020@20260416T054258Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T19:11:00.623899+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"gemini\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 3104.134, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Task T-021@20260416T054258Z completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS WITH NOTES.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-021@20260416T054258Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T20:03:07.350538+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 477.768, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_pass\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Task T-018@20260416T054258Za completed with outcome=success and verdict=PASS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-018@20260416T054258Za\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T20:13:00.719558+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndiff --git a/sdp/prd-snapshot.md b/sdp/prd-snapshot.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nindex 4ff5be6..16ccb8c 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--- a/sdp/prd-snapshot.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+++ b/sdp/prd-snapshot.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -1,288 +1,163 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# PRD Snapshot - PRD: CypherClaw Music Production Course Integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Source:** `my-claw/sdp/prd-music-production-course.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**SHA-256:** `2ed4ef622028ccd47ff58a0ebf97bf53ad6c16901cc35550eaa31b8bdd359ca9`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Captured:** 2026-04-16T05:42:58.472655+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PRD Snapshot - PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Source:** `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**SHA-256:** `65bcff28a80825e9c3dd33ed94a39f17a86a9e5d3d4c81aa9c271db4fb9b06ba`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Captured:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.336565+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# PRD: CypherClaw Music Production Course Integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ## Overview\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-CypherClaw now has a working score-tree and tracker-based songwriting spine,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-but the musical education layer still needs to be encoded as software behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-This PRD translates the CypherClaw Music Production Course into implementation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-work: theory, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, mixing, mastering, critical listening,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-SenseWeave interpretation, Theramini ensemble behavior, genre literacy, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-30-minute dramatic-arc production practice.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The goal is not to store a static course document. The goal is to make the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-course operational. CypherClaw should consult these ideas while composing,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-persist the resulting production choices in score trees and tracker metadata,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-verify them with tests/audio proxies, and use them during live playback.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-The production course is organized around the 30-minute dramatic arc:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Divination:** sparse listening, environmental responsiveness, wide space\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Emergence:** motifs and pulse forming, modal identity, opening filters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Conversation:** dialogue, counterpoint, call-and-response, development\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Convergence:** density, climax, harmonic/rhythmic/timbral saturation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- **Crystallization:** resolution, reduction, memory, reverb tail, archive\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Every requirement below should make that arc more musically literate and more\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-verifiable.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Depends on:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/sdp/prd-songwriter-emsd-completion.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `docs/cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `docs/cypherclaw-emsd-roadmap.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- current `ScoreTree`, composition gate, tracker compiler, tracker runtime,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  master bus, sample, self-listener, repertoire, and Theramini modules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Key files and modules:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/composition_gate.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/form_grammar.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/harmonic_planner.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/reharmonizer.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/hook_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/tracker_compiler.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker_runtime.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/arrangement_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/mix_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/ear_engine.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sound_palette_lab.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_lab.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/dsp_scene_lab.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/theramini_duet.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/repertoire_memory.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- new production-course support modules under `my-claw/tools/senseweave/`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Current State Analysis\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Implemented Foundation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Score trees already represent commission, brief, form, motifs, sections,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  harmonic plan, arrangement plan, narrative map, and metadata.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The composer can compile approved score trees into tracker scenes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The runtime can schedule tracker rows, apply some row automation, and publish\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  current state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Harmony, hooks, arrangement, mix, sound palette, sample, DSP, ear, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  repertoire helpers exist as first-pass modules.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- EMSD curriculum scaffolds exist and can be used as reference/curriculum\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  targets.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Remaining Production Gaps\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Pitch, scale, chord, voicing, and functional-harmony knowledge is scattered\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  and not consistently encoded in one verified musical vocabulary.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Rhythm currently uses duration cells, but not enough meter, swing,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  polyrhythm, phrase breath, metric modulation, or groove intent.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Counterpoint and motivic development exist only in partial metadata; they\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  need rules that can shape independent lanes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Synthesis, production, and mix choices are not yet explicitly selected from\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  the course concepts per arc phase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Critical listening metrics exist as first-pass proxies but do not yet feed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  production choices strongly enough.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- SenseWeave mappings need musical interpretation rules for room, membrane,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  garden, Theramini, archive, and network sources.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Genre literacy is not yet a strategy library that can influence form,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  rhythm, harmony, sound design, and arrangement.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- The 30-minute production score needs to become a runtime phase profile,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  not only prose.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Goals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Encode the course as a runtime production knowledge base with typed,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  testable concepts.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Make pitch, harmony, rhythm, counterpoint, synthesis, mix, and production\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  decisions visible in score-tree and tracker metadata.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Improve long-form musical variety without losing live safety.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Give each 30-minute arc phase a coherent production profile.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Make SenseWeave and Theramini inputs musically interpretable through course\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  concepts instead of arbitrary parameter mappings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Add automated verification that catches unmusical regressions such as flat\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  loops, single-note drones, harsh registers, muddy mixes, missing transitions,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  and phase-inappropriate density.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Non-Goals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not replace the existing score-tree/tracker runtime.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not require external music APIs or copyrighted training material.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not require real SuperCollider rendering for every unit test. Deterministic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  metadata tests and synthetic audio proxies are acceptable where live rendering\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  is impractical.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not make every piece complex. Divination and Crystallization may be sparse\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  by design, and micro pieces remain valid when complete.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Do not hardcode one style as CypherClaw's identity. Genre literacy should be\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  a strategy vocabulary, not an imitation machine.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Product Requirements\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| ID | Description | Priority | Tier | Acceptance Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-|---|---|---|---|---|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-001 | Create a production-course knowledge base that the composer can consult at runtime. | MUST | T1 | - course concepts are represented as typed data or markdown references with stable IDs<br/>- arc-phase profiles exist for Divination, Emergence, Conversation, Convergence, and Crystallization<br/>- tests verify all required chapters/phase profiles are present and loadable |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-002 | Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. | MUST | T1 | - library includes chromatic, major/minor, seven modes, pentatonic, whole-tone, octatonic, blues, Hirajoshi, In Sen, Pelog, Bhairav, Hungarian minor, Prometheus, and microtonal/ratio helpers<br/>- interval metadata includes semitones, consonance/dissonance, character, and arc-phase affinity<br/>- tests verify interval/scale pitch-class sets and MIDI/frequency conversion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-003 | Add chord construction and voicing support. | MUST | T1 | - triads, seventh chords, extended chords, altered dominants, suspended/add chords, drop voicings, close/open voicings, and rootless/guide-tone voicings are supported<br/>- voicing engine respects register limits and configured spacing<br/>- tests verify chord pitch classes, unique voicings, range safety, and smooth voice-leading choices |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-004 | Encode functional harmony and modulation strategies. | MUST | T1 | - harmonic planner can label tonic, subdominant, dominant, secondary dominant, modal-interchange, tritone-sub, chromatic-mediant, pedal, planing, and modulation functions<br/>- score trees expose harmonic function and transition intent per section<br/>- tests verify cadence resolution, pivot/common-tone modulation continuity, and phase-appropriate tension levels |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-005 | Expand rhythm, meter, groove, and time handling. | MUST | T1 | - rhythm engine supports 4/4, 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8, free/rubato, swing, shuffle, dotted cells, push/pull, polyrhythm, polymeter, and metric modulation<br/>- tracker metadata carries meter, subdivision, swing ratio, groove timing, and phrase breath without breaking deterministic row scheduling<br/>- tests verify IOI ratios, swing offsets, polyrhythm cycle length, and phase-specific meter policies |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-006 | Add counterpoint and linear voice-combination rules. | MUST | T1 | - arrangement/compiler can choose contrary, oblique, parallel, echo, commentary, and completion relationships between lanes<br/>- dissonance and resolution rules are available as metadata checks<br/>- tests verify independent lane contours, staggered climaxes, and no accidental lane crowding |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-007 | Add post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies. | SHOULD | T2 | - composer can request pitch-class sets, spectral partial-derived harmony, just-intonation ratios, and 24-TET/ratio pitch events when phase/style permits<br/>- SenseWeave spectral analysis can seed harmonic material<br/>- tests verify generated material remains bounded and tagged as post-tonal/spectral/microtonal |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-008 | Build a synthesis-architecture strategy registry. | MUST | T1 | - registry covers subtractive, FM, additive, granular, physical modeling, and spectral/FFT processing with safe parameter ranges and arc-phase affinities<br/>- score tree or tracker scenes can request synthesis architecture by production role<br/>- tests verify each architecture has role tags, macro controls, safe ranges, and fallbacks |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-009 | Add production-aware frequency allocation and EQ policy. | MUST | T1 | - mix engine assigns sub, bass, low-mid, midrange, upper-mid, presence, and air lanes to roles<br/>- production metadata includes HPF/LPF/EQ intent for bass, pad, lead, texture, noise, sample, and Theramini lanes<br/>- tests verify role frequency lanes avoid primary masking and preserve bass center policy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-010 | Add dynamics, compression, sidechain, and deference policy. | MUST | T1 | - production profile maps arc phase to dynamic range, compression intensity, transient policy, and sidechain/deference rules<br/>- Theramini and environmental transients can request generated-material ducking or silence<br/>- tests verify dynamic targets, sidechain metadata, and no over-compression in Divination/Crystallization |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-011 | Add spatial, reverb, and delay production profiles. | MUST | T1 | - phase profiles define stereo width, near/far depth, reverb size/decay/damping, delay style, and transition-space behavior<br/>- tracker scenes expose spatial intent and reverb/delay sends<br/>- tests verify wide sparse openings, clearer Conversation space, focused Convergence, and long Crystallization tails |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-012 | Complete mastering and loudness policy for installation playback. | MUST | T1 | - master policy targets installation-safe LUFS/peak ranges, limiter ceiling, broad EQ intent, and phase-specific dynamic contrast<br/>- automated proxies catch clipping, silence, harshness, and low-end runaway<br/>- tests verify master profiles and synthetic render/loudness proxies |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-013 | Implement critical-listening and psychoacoustic interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 | - ear engine or production evaluator exposes spectral balance, dynamic contour, spatial distribution, timbral quality, rhythmic activity, harmonic tension, masking risk, and equal-loudness compensation hints<br/>- feedback can modify future density, register, EQ, dynamics, and sound-palette choices<br/>- tests use synthetic events/audio features to verify correction decisions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-014 | Encode SenseWeave voice-to-music interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 | - room, membrane/contact mic, garden, Theramini, archive, and network sources have musical mappings for pitch, rhythm, density, harmony, timbre, mix, and deference<br/>- Perform-VE condenser/room mic fallback is represented as a source option<br/>- tests verify quiet/noisy room, rain/wind/contact vibration, garden inactivity, Theramini activity, archive recall, and network/weather mappings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-015 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | MUST | T1 | - policy supports listening first, complementary register, rhythmic sympathy, harmonic response intervals, accompaniment textures, call/response, imitation, commentary, completion, and silence<br/>- score/tracker metadata identifies current lead/support roles<br/>- tests verify no register crowding, no excessive overlap during human/Theramini gesture, and recovery to solo mode |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-016 | Add a genre-literacy strategy library. | MUST | T1 | - strategies exist for ambient/drone/generative, minimalism, jazz, IDM/electronic, classical/orchestral form, musique concrete/electroacoustic, spectral music, blues, world-music concepts, and post-rock/experimental builds<br/>- strategies can influence form, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, arrangement, and mix without hardcoding imitation<br/>- tests verify strategy selection, arc affinity, and no missing required genre strategy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-017 | Make the 30-minute production score executable. | MUST | T1 | - procedural arc exposes per-phase density, dynamic, harmonic, rhythm, timbre, spatial, compression, SenseWeave, and synthesis targets<br/>- score-tree commissioning and tracker compilation use those targets for long pieces and 5-minute proxy tests<br/>- tests verify the five-phase contour and phase-specific production metadata |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-018 | Add phase-transition composition techniques. | MUST | T1 | - transition planner supports pivot event, breath/silence, metric modulation, timbral morph, harmonic pivot chord, and common-tone bridge<br/>- adjacent sections share at least one continuity element unless a deliberate hard cut is tagged<br/>- tests verify no untagged abrupt phase jumps and valid transition metadata |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-019 | Build SuperCollider recipe references without coupling tests to live audio. | SHOULD | T2 | - reference recipes exist for MIDI-to-frequency, intervals, scales, chord voicings, swing, polyrhythm, subtractive, FM, additive, granular, physical modeling, spectral freeze, EQ, compression, sidechain, reverb, delay, master bus, groups, buses, patterns, and envelopes<br/>- recipes are discoverable from curriculum/reference docs<br/>- tests verify recipe files and required labels exist |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-020 | Wire production-course choices into score trees and tracker output. | MUST | T1 | - score trees carry production vocabulary for mode/scale, harmonic function, meter/groove, counterpoint relation, synthesis architecture, mix role, spatial intent, genre strategy, phase profile, and transition type<br/>- tracker scenes/steps preserve enough metadata for runtime scheduling and diagnostics<br/>- tests verify metadata survives compose -> gate -> compile -> schedule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-021 | Extend the composition gate with production-course checks. | MUST | T1 | - gate can reject phase-inappropriate density, missing harmonic/rhythm metadata, unsafe register, flat dynamics, missing transition continuity, missing mix role, and untagged genre/strategy choices for long pieces<br/>- intentionally sparse/micro pieces can pass when they carry valid sparse intent<br/>- tests cover both rejection and acceptance paths |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-022 | Add course-driven self-critique and revision targets. | SHOULD | T2 | - critique output names concrete course concepts behind failures, such as masking, no recurrence, no cadence, weak transition, over-compression, or unsupported density<br/>- bounded revision can adjust form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, or strategy without changing piece identity<br/>- tests verify at least one metric improves after revision |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-023 | Turn the production course into executable curriculum exercises. | SHOULD | T2 | - curriculum includes exercises/tests for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full arc production<br/>- exercise metadata includes objective, template, verifier, and expected features<br/>- tests verify curriculum completeness and runnable verifier stubs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-024 | Add operator diagnostics for production-course decisions. | SHOULD | T2 | - face/status/operator output can show current phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile, SenseWeave source, Theramini relation, and critique notes<br/>- diagnostics degrade gracefully when data is absent<br/>- tests verify status payload shape and no hallucinated unavailable fields |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-025 | Add end-to-end production-course integration tests. | MUST | T1 | - tests compose, gate, compile, schedule, and inspect a 5-minute proxy arc using production-course metadata<br/>- tests verify non-silent output proxy, no single-note long sections, phase contour, transition continuity, mix role allocation, and repertoire storage<br/>- tests run without live hardware and with mocked SenseWeave/Theramini inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Dependency Map\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-```text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-001 -> MPC-002, MPC-008, MPC-017, MPC-019\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-002 -> MPC-003, MPC-004, MPC-007\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-003 -> MPC-004, MPC-006, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-004 -> MPC-017, MPC-018, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-005 -> MPC-006, MPC-017, MPC-018, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-006 -> MPC-015, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-007 -> MPC-008, MPC-014, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-008 -> MPC-009, MPC-011, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-009 -> MPC-010, MPC-012, MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-010 -> MPC-012, MPC-015, MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-011 -> MPC-017, MPC-018, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-012 -> MPC-013, MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-013 -> MPC-014, MPC-022\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-014 -> MPC-015, MPC-017, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-015 -> MPC-020, MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-016 -> MPC-017, MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-017 -> MPC-018, MPC-020, MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-018 -> MPC-020, MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-019 -> MPC-023\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-020 -> MPC-021, MPC-024, MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-021 -> MPC-022, MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-022 -> MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-023 -> MPC-024\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-MPC-024 -> MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Suggested Implementation Phases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 1: Musical Vocabulary Runtime\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-001\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-002\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-003\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-004\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-005\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- establish verified pitch, harmony, chord, rhythm, and production-course data\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  that downstream modules can depend on.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 2: Production Strategy and Arc Profiles\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-008\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-009\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-010\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-011\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-012\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-017\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-018\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- make each arc phase produce coherent synthesis, mix, dynamics, space, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  transition decisions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 3: Listening, Environment, and Ensemble\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-006\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-007\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-013\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-014\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-015\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- connect critical listening, SenseWeave, Theramini, counterpoint, and spectral\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  material to concrete score-tree and runtime choices.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 4: Genre Literacy and Curriculum\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-016\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-019\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-023\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-024\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- turn the course into reusable references, strategy libraries, exercises, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  operator-visible diagnostics.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-### Phase 5: Integration, Gate, and Revision\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Focus requirements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-020\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-021\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-022\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- MPC-025\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-Goal:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- prove the production-course layer survives the full compose -> gate ->\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  compile -> schedule -> critique -> store path.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Verification Strategy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Unit tests for theory primitives: intervals, pitch classes, scales, modes,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  MIDI/frequency conversion, chord construction, voicing uniqueness, cadence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  labels, and rhythm IOI ratios.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Metadata tests for score-tree/tracker propagation: arc phase, production\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  strategy, synthesis architecture, mix role, spatial profile, transition type,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  genre strategy, and SenseWeave/Theramini relation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Synthetic audio/proxy tests for mix/master: clipping, silence, harshness,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  low-end runaway, rough spectral balance, rough loudness target, and dynamic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  contour.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Integration tests for 5-minute proxy arcs, mocked SenseWeave streams,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  mocked Theramini activity, repertoire storage, and course-driven critique.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Curriculum tests that ensure references, recipes, prompts, exercises, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  verifier stubs remain present as the course expands.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Rollout Notes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Load this PRD after the current songwriter/EMSD completion PRD.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Keep the initial implementation behind the current fractal-form chain so it\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  does not interrupt T-014 through T-020.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Prefer metadata and deterministic proxy verification before adding expensive\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  live SuperCollider rendering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-- Treat the production-course data as a compositional policy layer. Runtime\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  modules should be able to ignore unavailable inputs and fall back to safe\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-  phase defaults.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CypherClaw already composes legible music: score trees, section functions, production profiles, genre strategies, SenseWeave mappings. But the path from composed score to synthesized audio still renders too rigidly. Phrases don't breathe. Repeated motifs don't vary. Silence is a byproduct of scheduling rather than an intentional voice. Sensors occasionally read like one-to-one controllers rather than shaping aggregate intent. The result is the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"almost-human\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" failure mode: structurally competent, expressively flat.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The fix is not sprinkled randomness. The research literature is unambiguous on this: human expressive variance is **structured, not stochastic**. Random jitter is what produces the uncanny-valley failure, not what escapes it.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+This PRD installs a dedicated **rendering layer** — a compiler pass between composition (score-tree) and synthesis (SuperCollider) — that translates score structure into correlated, intentional deviations in timing, dynamics, articulation, and silence. The architecture is KTH-rule-system-style: a stack of ordered, pure-function rules, each reading score features and emitting event-level deviations, each toggleable and quantity-adjustable, each leaving provenance on every event so authors can ablate and debug.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Five principles govern the whole design:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+1. **Structured over stochastic.** Every deviation is a function of score/sensor features. Gaussian jitter is allowed only below the listener JND (~3–5 ms, ~2 velocity units) and only as a final polish *on top of* intentional deviations.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+2. **Hierarchical arcs.** Section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level arcs, which modulate note-level accents. Arcs compose multiplicatively.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+3. **Legible intent.** Every phrase declares an intent tag (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate). Parameters are chosen so the intent is perceptible.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+4. **Restraint as material.** Silence is scheduled, not residual. Density and silence budgets are maintained per voice and per section.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+5. **Machine identity preserved.** Grid-locked elements (ostinati, sequencers, polyrhythmic machines), superhuman precision, and alien timbres are deliberately *not* humanized. CypherClaw is a robot musician that has learned which things humans shape — not a robot pretending to be a violinist.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The goal is not realism. It is **legibility**: a listener should feel that CypherClaw *intended* each phrase — to build, to withhold, to answer the room.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Scope and non-goals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**In scope:** a new rendering stage between composition and synthesis; an Event/PerformanceIntent/SectionEnvelope data model with rule-stack provenance; a 12-rule render stack (R1–R12); a seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds; a replay harness; a rule-ablation debugger; a metrics-CI gate with anti-pattern detection; a performance-worm diagnostic; a bounded sensor-to-intent aggregation matrix.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Out of scope / non-goals:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Photorealistic human-performance imitation. CypherClaw is a robot musician, not a violinist simulator.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- General-purpose MIDI humanizer — this is not a plugin.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Sensor-driven note generation. Sensors modulate expression, never replace composition.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Machine-learning performance models in this phase. Rule-based KTH-style is interpretable, debuggable, and gateable with fixed metrics. Learned models can be added after the metric gate is stable.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Replacement of existing composition, production-course, or synthesis work. This layer sits *above* synthesis and *below* composition — it renders what the composer emits.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## The four phases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCH-001..CCH-010).** Data model, seeded-RNG plumbing, replay harness, rule-ablation debugger. At end of phase, existing pieces render bit-identically through the new pipeline with no rules active — just plumbing.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 2 — Core rule stack (CCH-011..CCH-021).** R1 Metric Accent, R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH parabolic), R3 Agogic Accent, R4 Duration Contrast, R5 Final Ritardando (Friberg–Sundberg square-root), R6 Punctuation+Breath, R7 Articulation Shaping, R8 Microtiming Polish (below JND). Role-filter gating so grid-locked voices skip the stack. Phrase-feature extraction via partitura. End-of-phase: single-voice melodic passages sound shaped, not flat; metric gate shows structured deviations vs. flat-line baseline.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 3 — Memory, silence, ensemble (CCH-022..CCH-029).** R9 Motif memory with LRU + variation menu + return-home decay. R10 Silence budgets with wind-voice lung-capacity caps. R11 Call-response gating. Section-level envelope compositing. Tempo-dependent swing (Friberg/Sundström). Arc-shape variety. Restraint as global dampener. End-of-phase: 5-minute generative pieces no longer feel looped; repetition-variance metrics pass thresholds.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Phase 4 — Sensor aggregation + narrative coupling (CCH-030..CCH-033).** R12 Sensor-to-intent matrix (smoothed IIR, hysteresis, aggregate intentions — never one-to-one). Bounded reactive delta track. Narrative engine → SectionEnvelope coupling. End-of-phase: installation responds legibly to audience presence without gimmicky mappings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Metrics-CI Gate + Diagnostics (CCH-034..CCH-040).** Metric battery, anti-pattern detection, performance-worm logger, CI integration, audio-rendered cross-check, provenance in exported audio metadata, listener-review workflow. Runs in parallel with rule-stack build-out; most checks land alongside the rule they validate.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Depends on\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `my-claw/sdp/prd-music-production-course.md` — the currently-executing PRD covering production profiles, harmonic library, SenseWeave mappings, genre strategies, phase transitions. Rules R1–R8 read phase profiles and harmonic-function metadata from that layer.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `docs/cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` — the score-tree composer this layer renders from.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` — reference for existing musicianship vocabulary.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Current `ScoreTree`, composition gate, tracker compiler, tracker runtime, master bus, self-listener, Theramini modules.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Key files and modules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/` package:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/events.py` — Event, PerformanceIntent, SectionEnvelope, IntentTag, Role dataclasses\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/seed.py` — per-stage sub-seed derivation, replay harness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/rules/` — one module per R-rule (metric_accent.py, phrase_arch.py, agogic.py, duration_contrast.py, final_rit.py, punctuation.py, articulation.py, microtiming.py, motif_memory.py, silence_budget.py, call_response.py, sensor_intent.py)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/pass_.py` — RenderPass framework, ordered rule stack, ablation support\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/features.py` — partitura-backed phrase/harmonic feature extraction\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/replay.py` — bit-identical (score, seed, delta_track) → performed_part reproduction\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/worm.py` — performance-worm logger and convex-hull diagnostic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/metrics.py` — IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR, GS, pitch H1, LZ76, tempo autocorrelation, silence coverage\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `render/antipatterns.py` — quantization-ghosting, dynamic-compression, motif-ossification, random-as-expression, symmetric-arc-uncanny, dead-silence detectors\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py` — score-tree nodes carry PerformanceIntent / SectionEnvelope metadata\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py` — emits score-tree with new metadata; composition seed threaded through\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/composition_gate.py` — gate checks new metadata present on all phrases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/music_tracker.py` / `music_tracker_runtime.py` — tracker scenes preserve Event metadata through compile → schedule\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/operator_diagnostics.py` — surface active rule stack, current phrase intent, worm snapshot\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_render_*.py` — per-rule, role-filter, replay, ablation, metric, anti-pattern tests\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Requirements\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| ID | Description | Priority | Tier | Acceptance criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+|----|-------------|----------|------|---------------------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-001 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-002 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines PerformanceIntent(phrase_id, arc_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-003 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-004 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | MUST | T1 | - IntentTag enum exists in `render/events.py` with exactly six values<br/>- composition gate rejects phrases missing intent_tag on long pieces<br/>- micro pieces may use punctuate as the default<br/>- tests verify enum completeness and gate rejection path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-005 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | MUST | T1 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-006 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | MUST | T1 | - `render/seed.py` exposes derive_seed(root_seed, path_tuple) returning deterministic 32-bit sub-seed<br/>- Event.seed_path records the exact path used so any randomness inside rules can be reproduced<br/>- tests verify same (root, path) always yields same sub-seed across process restarts and Python minor versions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-007 | Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. | MUST | T1 | - `recursive_composer.py` and `score_tree.py` extended to attach PerformanceIntent to every phrase node and SectionEnvelope to every section node<br/>- composer accepts an explicit composition_seed argument and produces byte-identical score trees for the same seed + brief<br/>- existing pieces still compose successfully; gate passes on unchanged repertoire<br/>- tests verify determinism (two runs same seed → equal score-tree hash) and metadata presence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-008 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | MUST | T1 | - OSC bundle schema documented in `my-claw/docs/render-osc-schema.md`<br/>- `music_tracker_runtime.py` serializes Event fields into Pbind-compatible dictionaries preserving rule_stack and seed_path<br/>- synth side (reference SC file under `my-claw/supercollider/render_contract.scd`) demonstrates reading and ignoring unknown keys gracefully<br/>- tests verify round-trip of a sample phrase through serialize → parse preserves all fields |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-009 | Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). | MUST | T1 | - `render/replay.py` exposes replay(score, seeds, delta_track) returning PerformedPart byte-identical to original<br/>- delta_track is persisted as JSON per run alongside audio output<br/>- tests verify: re-render with same inputs produces identical Event sequence (hash match) including all timing, velocity, and articulation values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-010 | Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. | MUST | T1 | - CLI or Python API `ablate(score, seeds, disabled_rules=[...])` returns alternate PerformedPart<br/>- output includes a diff report showing which Event fields changed vs. full-stack render<br/>- tests cover single-rule ablation, pair ablation, and all-rules-off (should equal bit-identical Phase-1 baseline) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-011 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | MUST | T1 | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-012 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-013 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-014 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-015 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-016 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-017 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-018 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-019 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-020 | Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | MUST | T1 | - all R1–R8 rules check `rule.applies_to(event.role)` before mutating the event<br/>- integration test: ostinato + melody passage renders with melody shaped and ostinato exactly quantized<br/>- gate test: passage where ostinato has non-zero timing_deviation_ms fails (indicates a rule leaked) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-021 | Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. | MUST | T1 | - `render/features.py` wraps partitura load_score + per-phrase feature computation<br/>- features annotated onto Events during score-tree → Event-list conversion<br/>- harmonic_charge uses tonal-pitch-space distance (Lerdahl) normalized 0..1<br/>- tests on known-score fixtures verify expected feature values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-022 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-023 | Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/silence_budget.py` maintains rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density)·dt per voice<br/>- when rest_budget exceeds threshold at phrase boundary, either extends breath (via R6) or drops next phrase to tacet<br/>- tests verify accumulator math, threshold trigger, and tacet-drop path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-024 | Implement wind/voice lung-capacity constraints: 4–8 s continuous-play cap per instrument-sim voice. | MUST | T1 | - voices with lung_capacity set (default 6 s for winds/voice, null for others) track continuous sounding time<br/>- exceeding cap forces a breath at next phrase boundary or earlier if density tolerates<br/>- tests verify cap enforcement and breath insertion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-025 | Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-026 | Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. | MUST | T1 | - at each event, final_tempo_mult = section_envelope.tempo_base(t) × phrase_arch.tempo_mult(x) × (1 + sensor_tempo_scale)<br/>- clamp composed result to ±15% bounds<br/>- tests verify multiplicative composition and clamp behavior |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-027 | Implement tempo-dependent swing curve per Friberg/Sundström (3.5:1 at slow tempi down toward 1:1 at fast), with short-note near-constant ~100 ms. | MUST | T1 | - swing ratio computed from current tempo rather than fixed global setting<br/>- short-note duration held near 100 ms across tempo range<br/>- optional role-specific override (cymbal uses ride ratio, soloists use Benadon BUR 1.2–1.7)<br/>- tests verify ratio curve and short-note invariance |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-028 | Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. | MUST | T1 | - arc_shape selected from PerformanceIntent or, if unspecified, sampled from authored distribution weighted by intent_tag<br/>- for intent_tag=withhold, occasional flat arc (tempo_deviation_pct=0) is expressive<br/>- tests verify shape distribution over many phrases and flat-arc presence for withhold intent |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-029 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | MUST | T1 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-030 | Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/sensor_intent.py` takes raw SenseWeave sensor stream, applies one-pole IIR smoothing (α≈0.1), threshold with hysteresis, and multiplies by sensor→intention weight matrix<br/>- outputs aggregate_intentions, never direct synth parameters<br/>- listener-reverse-engineer test: given recorded sensor stream and rendered output, no single sensor can be shown to drive any single synth parameter at correlation > 0.85 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-031 | Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. | MUST | T1 | - scheduler writes sensor_tempo_scale ∈ [0.92, 1.08], sensor_amp_scale ∈ [0.80, 1.20], sensor_brightness ∈ [-1.0, +1.0] onto each Event<br/>- delta track is persisted as JSON alongside audio output for replay<br/>- out-of-bounds values clamped and logged<br/>- tests verify clamping, persistence, and replay consumes the delta track |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-032 | Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. | SHOULD | T2 | - narrative beat → SectionEnvelope mapping exposed via existing narrative engine interface<br/>- section choice respects tension_trajectory + tone_vector from narrative tone controller<br/>- tests use fixture beats and verify expected section envelopes selected |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-033 | Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. | MUST | T1 | - `operator_diagnostics.py` extended with aggregate_intentions block<br/>- raw sensor values are NOT surfaced alongside synth parameters in diagnostics (prevents accidentally re-introducing gimmicky reverse-mappings)<br/>- tests verify telemetry shape and absence of raw pairings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-034 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | MUST | T1 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, DNVR 0.25–0.7, pitch H1 2.3–3.0, GS 0.6–0.9, tempo ρ₁ 0.7–0.95, LZ76 0.4–0.7, ≥1 novelty peak per phrase, ≥100 ms silence at phrase boundaries<br/>- tests run metrics on rule-disabled flat-line control (should fail pass bands) and full-stack render (should pass) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-035 | Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. | MUST | T1 | - `render/antipatterns.py` implements each detector<br/>- quantization ghosting: velocity σ > 0 AND timing σ < 3 ms → fail<br/>- dynamic compression: velocity range < 20 → fail<br/>- motif ossification: GS > 0.95 across repeated sections → fail<br/>- random-as-expression: Ljung-Box fails to reject white noise on tempo or velocity series → fail<br/>- symmetric-arc uncanny: per-phrase worm convex-hull shape variance < 5% across phrases → fail<br/>- dead-silence failure: no rests ≥200 ms in a 2-minute melodic passage → fail<br/>- each detector has a positive fixture (should fail) and negative fixture (should pass) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-036 | Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. | MUST | T1 | - `render/worm.py` emits per-piece worm JSON and PNG to `artifacts/worms/<piece_id>/`<br/>- convex-hull area computed via scipy.spatial.ConvexHull<br/>- reject point-worm (mechanical: area < 1.0) and space-filling worm (random: area > saturation threshold)<br/>- CI attaches worm PNGs to build artifacts for listener review |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-037 | Integrate metric battery + anti-pattern detectors into CI gate with fail-on-regression policy. | MUST | T1 | - pytest gate runs metrics on a curated fixture set of 5-minute rendered pieces<br/>- any metric outside pass band or any anti-pattern trigger fails the build<br/>- pass bands are per-intent-tag where applicable (withhold-tagged phrases allow lower velocity σ)<br/>- tests verify a deliberately broken render fails the gate and a healthy render passes |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-038 | Build audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty cross-check via librosa on the actual rendered audio. | SHOULD | T2 | - offline renderer produces 5-minute proxy audio for fixture pieces<br/>- librosa self-similarity matrix + Foote novelty curve extracted<br/>- symbolic novelty peaks (from CCH-034) must align with audio novelty peaks within ±500 ms<br/>- catches cases where symbolic metrics look fine but synthesis flattens expression |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-039 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | MUST | T1 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| CCH-040 | Establish listener-review workflow: weekly rendered pieces tagged with rule-stack provenance, ablation tooling documented for operators, review log template in place. | SHOULD | T2 | - `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` describes cadence, how to ablate a rule, how to attach a review note<br/>- weekly review log at `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` with template entries (piece, date, felt-wrong symptom, suspected rule, ablation result, action)<br/>- tests: doc and template exist and link to the ablation CLI from CCH-010 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Acceptance criteria (top-level)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+1. End-to-end: existing pieces render bit-identically through the new pipeline when all rules are disabled (Phase 1 plumbing is transparent).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+2. With R1–R8 enabled, single-voice melodic passages show structured velocity + timing deviations matching research pass bands (CCH-034).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+3. Grid-locked voices (ostinato, perc) emerge from full-stack render with timing_deviation_ms == 0 — machine identity preserved.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+4. Motif Memory (R9) produces at least one variation per recurrence and returns to the home motif within ~8 iterations.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+5. Silence Budget (R10) enforces ≥100 ms silence at every phrase boundary on melodic voices in a 2-minute rendered fixture.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+6. Call-Response Gating (R11) on a 2-voice leader/follower fixture produces complementary phrase shapes (verifiable via phrase-apex correlation < -0.3).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+7. Sensor Aggregation (R12) passes the reverse-engineer test: no single sensor correlates > 0.85 with any single synth parameter over a 5-minute rendered run with recorded sensor stream.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+8. Replay harness reproduces past performances byte-identically given (score, seeds, delta_track).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+9. Rule-ablation debugger produces a human-readable diff of which Event fields changed when a rule is disabled.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+10. Metric battery + anti-pattern detectors integrated into CI; a deliberate regression (e.g., microtiming σ bumped to 50 ms, velocity range compressed to 5) fails the gate.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+11. Performance-worm PNG is attached to CI artifacts for every fixture piece.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+12. Rule-stack provenance present in every exported `.render.json` sidecar.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+13. Operator diagnostics expose aggregate intentions (global_energy/restraint/brightness) but NOT raw one-to-one sensor→parameter pairings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+14. Existing PromptClaw \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Music Production Course Integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" PRD tasks remain compatible — this layer consumes production-course metadata (phase profile, harmonic function, spatial intent, mix role) from Events without modification.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Research basis (reference)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **KTH rule system** (Friberg, Sundberg, Frydén, 1978–2006; Director Musices). Phrase Arch, Duration Contrast, Melodic + Harmonic Charge, Final Ritardando, Punctuation rules with per-rule quantity k.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Todd 1985/1992** — parabolic tempo + loudness arcs aligned with phrase structure.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Widmer (JKU Linz)** — ML performance models validating \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"stress the apex of up-down contour\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" and related local principles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Friberg & Sundström** — ride-cymbal swing ratio 3.5:1 at slow tempi → ~1:1 at fast; short note ~100 ms near-constant.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Benadon** — soloist BUR 1.2–1.7 typically less swung than cymbal.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Friberg & Sundberg 1995** — listener JND for isochronous perturbation ~10 ms.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Senn et al. 2016 / Butterfield 2010** — groove microtiming within ±50 ms, mostly under 30 ms.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Lerdahl tonal pitch space** — harmonic charge via pitch-space distance + dissonance + attraction.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Huron 2006 (Sweet Anticipation) / Margulis / Farbood 2012** — tension modeling (ITPRA; surprise/denial/expectancy).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Goebl & Palmer 2009 / Keller 2008 / Large & Palmer 2002** — ensemble adaptation argues for internal \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"listening\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" state even when solo.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Savery, Rose & Weinberg 2019 (Shimon)** — prosody-as-robot-identity; commit to machine identity rather than pretend.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **partitura / Basis Mixer / ACCompanion (CP-JKU, MEC 2022, IJCAI 2023)** — architectural pattern for symbolic-score → performed-part stages.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Câmara et al. 2022 / Repp 1992** — expressive variance is structured, not stochastic.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Anti-patterns to reject (built into CI)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Random-as-expression.** Gaussian jitter without structured deviation. Ljung-Box must reject white-noise null on tempo and velocity series.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Enthusiastic rule application.** Doubling every k produces caricature, not more expression. Defaults are calibrated and per-piece overrides must be justified.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Forgetting machine identity.** If a rule leaks onto grid-locked voices, the render fails the role-filter gate.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **One-to-one sensor gimmickry.** No listener-reverse-engineerable sensor → parameter mapping.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Symmetric-arc uncanny.** Every phrase cannot have the same parabolic shape.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Permanent novelty / no return home.** Motif memory must bring the original back within ~8 iterations.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Dead-silence failure.** A 2-minute melodic passage with no rests ≥200 ms fails — silence is a first-class voice.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndiff --git a/sdp/requirements-register.md b/sdp/requirements-register.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nindex 35ffd6a..f31011e 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--- a/sdp/requirements-register.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+++ b/sdp/requirements-register.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -1,32 +1,47 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-# Requirements Register — PRD: CypherClaw Music Production Course Integration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Requirements Register — PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Extracted:** 2026-04-16T05:42:58.472602+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Total requirements:** 25\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Extracted:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.336519+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Total requirements:** 40\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n | ID | Description | Priority | Tier | Section |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n |----|-------------|----------|------|---------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-001 | Create a production-course knowledge base that the composer can consult at runtime. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-002 | Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-003 | Add chord construction and voicing support. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-004 | Encode functional harmony and modulation strategies. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-005 | Expand rhythm, meter, groove, and time handling. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-006 | Add counterpoint and linear voice-combination rules. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| MPC-007 | Add post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies.