 ## Unreleased
 
+- Added depth-2 PromptClaw path layouts (frac-0041): `promptclaw/paths.py` now exposes a frozen `RunPathLayout` plus `ProjectPaths.run_layout()`, `ProjectPaths.ensure_run_layout()`, and `ProjectPaths.path_summary()` so project/run filesystem contracts can produce typed layouts, idempotently prepare run directories, and emit JSON-safe operator summaries. Existing project-level path attributes and `run_*` helper return values are preserved; `ArtifactManager.create_run_layout()` now iterates the canonical run layout while keeping the same on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` structure. Empty run ids fail fast with `ValueError` before layout creation. `tests/test_promptclaw_paths_depth.py` pins helper compatibility, JSON-safe summaries, layout preparation through `ArtifactManager`, run-id rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; config, orchestrator, artifact, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
+
 - Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifacts read path (frac-0040): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes `ArtifactManager.read_events()` which parses `events.jsonl` line by line and reconstructs the same `Event` dataclass shape that `append_event()` writes, returning `[]` when the log file does not yet exist. The four filename-taking write helpers (`write_prompt`, `write_output`, `write_handoff`, `write_summary`) now reject empty/whitespace-only filenames with `ValueError` before any I/O, matching the orchestrator's existing call-site contract while failing fast at the boundary. Existing public method signatures, on-disk filenames, JSONL serialization shape, and orchestrator call sites are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_depth.py` pins the round-trip read, missing-log empty result, empty-filename rejection across the four filename helpers, normal-filename acceptance, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` and `tests/test_config.py` remain the regression anchors for end-to-end run behavior and config loading.
 
 - Added depth-2 PromptClaw model diagnostics (frac-0039): `promptclaw/models.py` now exposes a frozen `ConfigModelReport` plus typed helpers `sorted_agents`, `summarize_agent`, `config_model_report`, `summarize_config_model`, `summarize_route_decision`, and `summarize_run_state` so config, route, agent, and run dataclasses can emit deterministic JSON-safe operator summaries without changing existing dataclass fields or orchestration call sites. The narrative ASGI entry point `cypherclaw.narrative_api.main:app` now calls `bootstrap_identity()` before app creation, matching the `python -m cypherclaw.narrative_api` startup path so first boots mint and persist identity automatically. `tests/test_promptclaw_models_depth.py` pins model summary counts, sorted JSON-safe output, route/run summaries, an end-to-end orchestrator run summary, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_narrative_api_main.py` now pins ASGI import identity persistence between boots, while existing config/router/orchestrator and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
